		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Francis Ford Coppola</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<table class="infobox vcard vevent" style="width:22em; font-size:90%; text-align:left;">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center; font-size:larger; background-color:#ed8; color:#000;" class="fn summary">Francis Ford Coppola</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="padding: 0px; padding-top: 2px; text-align:center; font-size:100%;" class=""><a href="/wiki/File:Francis_Ford_Coppola(CannesPhotoCall)_crop.jpg" class="image" title="Francis Ford Coppola(CannesPhotoCall) crop.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Francis_Ford_Coppola%28CannesPhotoCall%29_crop.jpg/180px-Francis_Ford_Coppola%28CannesPhotoCall%29_crop.jpg" width="180" height="228" border="0" /></a><br />
<small>Coppola at <a href="/wiki/Cannes_Film_Festival" title="Cannes Film Festival">Cannes</a>, <a href="/wiki/2001_in_film" title="2001 in film">2001</a>.</small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Born</th>
<td>April 7, 1939 <span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1939-04-07</span>)</span> <span class="noprint">(age&#160;69)</span><br />
<a href="/wiki/Detroit" title="Detroit">Detroit</a>, <a href="/wiki/Michigan" title="Michigan">Michigan</a>, <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">U.S.</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Occupation</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a>, <a href="/wiki/Film_producer" title="Film producer">producer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><span style="white-space:nowrap;">Spouse(s)</span></th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Eleanor_Coppola" title="Eleanor Coppola">Eleanor Jessie Neil</a> (1963-present)</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Francis Ford Coppola</b> (born April 7, 1939) is a five-time <a href="/wiki/Academy_Award" title="Academy Award">Academy Award</a>-winning <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a>, <a href="/wiki/Film_producer" title="Film producer">producer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a>. Away from showbusiness, Coppola is also a <a href="/wiki/Vintner" title="Vintner" class="mw-redirect">vintner</a>, <a href="/wiki/Publisher" title="Publisher" class="mw-redirect">magazine publisher</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hotel_manager" title="Hotel manager">hotelier</a>. He is a graduate of <a href="/wiki/Hofstra_University" title="Hofstra University">Hofstra University</a> where he studied theatre. He earned an <a href="/wiki/Master_of_Fine_Arts" title="Master of Fine Arts">M.F.A.</a> in film directing from the <a href="/wiki/UCLA_Film_School" title="UCLA Film School" class="mw-redirect">UCLA Film School</a>. He is most renowned for directing the highly regarded <i><a href="/wiki/The_Godfather" title="The Godfather">Godfather</a></i> films, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Conversation" title="The Conversation">The Conversation</a></i>, and the <a href="/wiki/Vietnam_War" title="Vietnam War">Vietnam War</a> <a href="/wiki/Epic_film" title="Epic film">epic</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Apocalypse_Now" title="Apocalypse Now">Apocalypse Now</a></i>.</p>
