<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917585,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917585,00.html" rel="nofollow">"Citizen Coppola"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)">Time</a>. 1975-06-30<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917585,00.html" class="external free" title="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917585,00.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917585,00.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-05-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Citizen+Coppola&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=1975-06-30&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BTime+%28magazine%29%7CTime%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.time.com%2Ftime%2Fmagazine%2Farticle%2F0%2C9171%2C917585%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Francis_Ford_Coppola"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> This had previously been accomplished seven times, by six different directors, between 1937 and 1943, when the Academy announced ten nominees yearly. Coppola's feat would later be matched by <a href="/wiki/Herbert_Ross" title="Herbert Ross">Herbert Ross</a> in 1978, with <i><a href="/wiki/The_Goodbye_Girl" title="The Goodbye Girl">The Goodbye Girl</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/The_Turning_Point_(1977_film)" title="The Turning Point (1977 film)">The Turning Point</a></i>, and <a href="/wiki/Steven_Soderbergh" title="Steven Soderbergh">Steven Soderbergh</a> in 2001, with <i><a href="/wiki/Erin_Brockovich_(film)" title="Erin Brockovich (film)">Erin Brockovich</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Traffic_(2000_film)" title="Traffic (2000 film)">Traffic</a></i>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMurray.2C_Noel2005">Murray, Noel (2005-11-16). <a href="http://avclub.com/content/node/42688" class="external text" title="http://avclub.com/content/node/42688" rel="nofollow">"Hammett"</a>. <a href="/wiki/The_A.V._Club" title="The A.V. Club">The A.V. Club</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://avclub.com/content/node/42688" class="external free" title="http://avclub.com/content/node/42688" rel="nofollow">http://avclub.com/content/node/42688</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-05-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Hammett&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Murray%2C+Noel&amp;rft.au=Murray%2C+Noel&amp;rft.date=2005-11-16&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BThe+A.V.+Club%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Favclub.com%2Fcontent%2Fnode%2F42688&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Francis_Ford_Coppola"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
